What Information we collect and How we use it
Apple Health and Motion data
In order to process data to perform sleep analysis and understanding of sleep habits and of how sleep quality is correlated to certain health and motion metrics, Rem relies on the ability to read your health data for sleep analysis from the Apple HealthKit database and the data recorded by the motion sensors on your iPhone and Apple Watch. Rem will ask for your explicit permission to access specified categories of health data and recorded data by the motion sensors that are stored on your device through Apple Health. Rem cannot read data from the Apple HealthKit database and Motion and Fitness Activity unless you specifically grant access.
Anonymous usage data and third-party analytics
We may use third-party services in Rem in order to detect and diagnose any potential issues and understand how Rem is used so that we can improve your overall experience with Rem. We never share any of your sleep or health data with any of those services. Those third-party services may use and store anonymous aggregate data such as the IP addresses or device identifiers of the devices, device characteristics, location data, version of Rem installed on your device, the iOS version that your device is running on and whether or not you have access to our premium features. We will not sell your Health Data to advertising platforms, affiliate networks, data brokers or information resellers. We will not use your Health Data for advertising, promotion, cross-selling or any similar service.
